// TKT-suppress-telegram-menu-restart-loop
// Disable auto-registered native bot menu for all 3 Telegram accounts to stop
// the 66-command menu sync churn that triggers the supervisor auto-restart loop.
//
// Path: channels.telegram.accounts.<id>.commands.{native,nativeSkills}
//
// Per OpenClaw source (bot-CBwSxkGA.js, bot-deps-DdimKfyx.js,
// commands-D_2azr8j.js, extensions/telegram/openclaw.plugin.json):
//   - The Telegram plugin sets `nativeCommandsAutoEnabled: true` and
//     `nativeSkillsAutoEnabled: true` as read-only command defaults.
//   - With 15 agents + 5 enabled skills + 45 built-in native commands, the
//     resolved catalog hits 66 commands which fits the 100-command hard cap
//     but the 5700-character description payload budget is being trimmed on
//     every sync, producing the "menu text exceeded the conservative
//     5700-character payload budget" log line and contributing to channel
//     supervisor churn.
//   - 5700-char budget and 100-command cap are hard-coded constants in
//     bot-deps-DdimKfyx.js (TELEGRAM_TOTAL_COMMAND_TEXT_BUDGET,
//     TELEGRAM_MAX_COMMANDS). They are NOT user-configurable.
//   - Per-account override IS supported (configSchema validates
//     accounts.<id>.commands.{native,nativeSkills}).
//
// This is a config-only change. NO Gateway restart is required by the
// runtime: the bot reads `telegramCfg.commands` lazily via
// resolveFreshTelegramConfig in the polling loop, so the new values take
// effect on the next sync cycle (a few seconds). A graceful Gateway
// restart is still recommended to confirm clean state.
//
// Security/CHG notes (Yoda review):
//   - Does NOT alter botToken, allowFrom, groupAllowFrom, or any secrets
//     provider entry.
//   - Does NOT change the `bindings` (foodie -> Foodie account stays).
//   - Net effect: bot menu (the Telegram "/" command picker) is empty.
//     Slash commands can still be typed manually because the runtime
//     resolves them via text routing, not the Bot API menu. The message
//     pipeline is untouched.
//
// Apply with: see apply section at bottom.
{
  "channels": {
    "telegram": {
      "accounts": {
        "yoda": {
          "commands": {
            "native": false,
            "nativeSkills": false
          }
        },
        "aria": {
          "commands": {
            "native": false,
            "nativeSkills": false
          }
        },
        "Foodie": {
          "commands": {
            "native": false,
            "nativeSkills": false
          }
        }
      }
    }
  }
}

